links.title: A Giant Fund Bought More Apple, AMD, and Equinix Stock. Here's What It Sold. - Barron's
links.description: A giant pension made major changes in its U.S.-listed stock investments. PGGM of Zeist, Netherlands, bought more Apple (ticker: AAPL) stock, and materially added to investments in Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) and Equinix (EQIX) in the third quarter. The pension also slashed a third of its stake in Simon Property Group (SPG) during the quarter.

links.title: Apple hires former Tesla engineer
links.description: Apple has hired a former engineer from Tesla to boost its car-development efforts, Bloomberg News reported, citing people with knowledge of the matter. Cupertino, California-based Apple has tapped Christopher Moore for its team working on a self-driving car, the report said. Apple and Tesla did not immediately respond to Reuters requests for comment.
